          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A woods-saxon and double-folding optical-model",
                " description of 14N elastic and inelastic scattering",
                " from 24Mg, 27Al and 28Si"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDGT"
                ],
                "institute": "1USAFSU"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " FSU Super FN tandem Van de Graaff",
                " accelerator"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Molecular nitrogen beams, NH- and NH-2"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " three silicon surface barrier detectors which",
                " were separated by lab angles of 10 degree."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "For the 27Al and 28S measurements, self-supporting",
                " 27Al and 28SiO2 foils with thicknesses of",
                " approximately 100 microg/cm2 were used. The 24Mg",
                " measurements were performed with carbon-backed 24Mg",
                " targets whose thicknesses ranged from 150 to 175",
                " micropg/cm2. The 24Mg and 28Si targets were",
                " isotopically enriched to about 99 %."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "14N"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The determination of the product of the detector solid",
                " angle and target thickness, necessary to establish an",
                " absolute cross section for each measurement, was made",
                " by scattering 20 MeV 14N from the 24Mg, 27Al and 28Si",
                " targets at forward angles where deviations from the",
                " Rutherford cross section are small."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
